Operates compatible shortcuts to improve code quality and provide data integrity assurance.
If the shortcut input is the Integrity framework command “identify,” exit with the initializing shortcut dictionary.

Check the first item in the shortcut input stack for a target shortcut.
If the item is a dictionary, check for a value at key “input” and assign it to the target shortcut’s “Shortcut Input” variable. Then check for a value at key “name”.
If no dictionary is found, but there is valid text, assume it may be the target shortcut’s name.
